    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The driven pulley speed sensor is mounted on the transmission case. The driven pulley speed sensor contains a semiconductor that detects the driven pulley position. As the driven pulley rotates, the magnetic flux of the driven pulley speed sensor fluctuates. The magnetic flux variation is converted into a pulse signal and sent to the PGM-FI ECU. The direction of rotation of the rotor is detected by the voltage level of the pulse signal. If there is a discrepancy between the vehicle running status and the direction of rotation indicated by the pulse signal, the PGM-FI ECU determines a failure and stores the DTC."
    },
